{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18c4c6bc-6069-4c80-8b9c-c18397e32858","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n**Environment variables** (container spec):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  # Enable automatic crash dumps\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"\n  # Path to createdump (required for NativeAOT — it's not bundled)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n  # Dump file naming pattern (%e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... existing config ...\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi            # adjust to your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory. Without it, dump generation silently fails.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is critical for NativeAOT since the tool isn't co-located with the runtime.\n- **`emptyDir`** is fine for transient collection; swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- For debugging, add `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` to get verbose logging from `createdump` to stderr.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4634c0bf-a0bb-4112-aba7-91b0fd39a7f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking me to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app in Kubernetes. Let me provide the configuration they need.\n\nFor .NET crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic dump generation on crash\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` — full dump (1=mini, 2=heap, 3=triage, 4=full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n\n\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` — optional, enables diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nFor NativeAOT apps, there's a critical difference: the runtime needs to know where to find the `createdump` tool, so I'll need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to point to the createdump binary location.\n\nThe key environment variables are `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` for full dumps or 2 for heap-only, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` to specify the output path, and `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` which is especially important for NativeAOT since the tool isn't bundled with the app.\n\nFor Kubernetes deployment, I need to configure environment variables on the container, set up a volume to persist the dumps, and potentially grant the SYS_PTRACE capability so createdump can actually work.","outputTokens":994,"requestId":"5FC1:36F7E:DA834E:FDCF22:69EACA6E"},"id":"21e8e66f-7ee2-426c-8287-97591189e144","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:42:25.527Z","parentId":"477530fc-bde1-4377-a54b-c07e56006371"}
